Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper discusses indoor wireless communication, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper talks about high data rate transmission, which is a key aspect of information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the capacity to accommodate more users, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high bandwidth. 
4. cs.OH (Other Computer Science) - This paper could also fall under the category of "Other Computer Science" as it covers a broad range of topics related to Li-Fi based indoor communication. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a Li-Fi based communication model and evaluates its performance under different scenarios, which involves computational engineering.
